The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Wednesday, October 23, 2002 				 No free lunch
																								Calcutta, Oct. 22: Three meals a day in the states teaching hospitals  now served free  will cost the patients Rs 28 from November 1. 																								Only patients with below-poverty-line cards will not have to pay for their meals, health department sources said today.																								The patients in the eight teaching hospitals, including five in the city, will be provided cooked food from outside. Dieticians at the hospitals will certify if the food is palatable, fresh and nutritious.																								The caterers will have to produce specimen of the cooked food to the hospital superintendents before serving them. 
